25:
Dia, you're even more incredible on
the inside! Such fine mechanics! I
wonder what this one does...
30:
This is a little embarrassing,
Luciada...
38:
That flying golem just now... What's it
called again? A drone? And are they
remote-controlled, or do they make
their own decisions?
43:
Eeeek! Golem research is going to
be so much easier now with all
these books! New ideas are already
flooding in!
46:
My hands are shaking from all this
inspiration!
55:
You're in Starview's infirmary. You
collapsed.
63:
You've been working too hard! I was
worried about you, you know?
70:
I have been very busy with my usual
student council work as well as the
correspondence with the Farlands...
74:
Are you all right, Luciada? Do you
have a headache? How anchored
do you feel to reality?
78:
Hm? Um, I feel fine... Much better
now, actually, after that rest.
81:
...I see. You've embraced the shifts
and made them your own. You're a
brilliant pupil, Luciada.
84:
I can't say I fully understand... but
thank you?
89: No. You need to keep resting.
92:
Sleep deprivation impairs one's
brain function. Such individuals tend
to become impatient, which in turn
makes rest even more difficult. It's
extremely illogical.
96:
Gather your courage, and get under
the blanket. That is all.
100:
B-but everything's okay now, right?
And I've nearly finished a new theory
on golem construction—
112:
...To be honest, I was starting to feel
like I was doing a little too much.
119: I need to calm down a little, don't I...
123: All right, I've made up my mind!
127:
I will resign as student council
president!
134:
I was thinking about it... Why did I
decide to leave the Farlands and
attend Voluntas Academy?
140:
So why in the world am I the
president of the student council?!
My priorities are all out of order!
146:
And just think—it's the perfect
opportunity.
149:
Magia Fest caused a lot of damage,
in a lot of ways.
153:
So I'll take responsibility for it by
choosing to step down from my
position!
170:
Your attendant is being tracked
down by the academy.
173:
It seems that the serpent sample
was used in the way it was to draw
out the person of interest. Things
may have gone beyond what was
expected, however...
175:
This means that this is the
academy's responsibility, not yours.
You can forget about it now.
178:
...Mr. Liam. Surely you don't believe
that I could simply forget about it
like that.
186: Oh, Luciada! How're you feeling now?
194: Uh... Doesn't look that way at all...
205:
They immediately held a new
election... And I was re-elected!
209:
Come on! How?! I wasn't even
running!
213:
Just what exactly IS a "special
recommended candidate"?!
217:
They trust you a lot, right? I don't
think it's so strange that they
elected you again.
220:
You say you're not sure whether the
other students see you as their real
student council president... but I'm
sure they do.
237:
That's right, I don't! But if they chose
to elect me again, I guess my hands
are tied.
239:
Regardless of what's going on in the
Farlands and no matter what the
Sextans or other Nine Houses might
want...
243:
I will simply follow my own heart and
push for stronger relations between
Shibuya and Palpebra!
257:
This means I still won't have enough
time to do my research...
264:
Then... that means I don't have any
choice but to cut back on my sleep!
274: C-come on! Mr. Liam, where are you!
277:
Help me come up with a logical
solution to all this!
